The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Sona Koyo lines up unit in Haryana

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: Sona Koyo Steering Systems plans to set up an electronic power steering plant in Daruhera (Haryana).

 The plant will have an installed capacity of 1 lakh units. We have already received an order of 50,000 units from General Motors India, Sono Koyo Steering Systems chairman and managing director Surinder Kapur said on the sidelines of a conference organised by the CII.

 The plant, which will see an investment of Rs 35 crore, is expected to go on stream next year, he said.

 The firm has bagged an order for manufacturing electronic power systems for GMs new car ? D200. The order has to be completed by 2007, said Kapur. 




